The standard group women network today held its first awards ceremony that aimed to celebrate men and women who are making a difference in the society. The auspicious event took place at the standard group offices along mombasa road and was graced by standard group CEO Orlando Lyomu, human resource manager Nicholas Siwatom and the executive director of amnesty international Houghton Irungu. The winners were Mercy Githinji who won the employee of the year award, Ali Manzu for gender equality category, Anne Gitau for public service champion and Mike Nyagwoka for the category of championing for people with disability at work among others.